A hazifeladat a kovetkezo:
* Telepitsetek virtualboxot
* Toltsetek le a legfrissebb ubuntut (desktop)
* telepitsetek a virtualboxban
  * Ha megakadtok barhol, keressetek fel nyugodtan
* Telepitsetek egy VSCode – ot az ubuntun belul
  * opcionalisan a sajat gepeteken is lehet, de elso sorban egy egyseges fejlesztesi konyzetetet szeretnek harmotoknak : )


VSCode telepites:
·         Download Visual Studio Code for Linux
·         Extract it: unzip VSCode-linux-x64.zip -d ~/path/to/VSCode
·         Run the code executable to open Visual Studio Code
·         (Optional) Create a symbolic link to conveniently run code from the terminal:
·         sudo ln -s /path/to/VSCode/code /usr/local/bin/code

Bonus:
Tedd a vscode program indito linkjet a $HOME/bin be,
s a bash profile-ban allitsad be hogy ez a mappa legyen nezve terminal parancs inditasokkor.

#######
VirtualBox install: done
Ubuntu install: done
Visual Studio Code install: done (using software center in Ubuntu)
Created bin directory inside the $HOME directory: /home/itorok/bin
Copied the VSCode link by drag and drop to the bin folder. Modified permission to allow running the file. (all done through the graphical interface. I have no idea how to do the same using terminal.)
Updated the .bashrc file in the ~ directory: added "cd /home/itorok/bin" to the end of the file. Since then all terminals open like this:
